The paper focuses on using Convolutional Neural Networks for image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of transfer learning and the Squeeze-and-Excitation architecture also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the challenges of image analysis in marine ecology, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or multimedia (cs.MM) categories.
